
# create an issue branch

$[main] git pull // confirm you are on 'main'; pull changes

$[main] git switch -c <issue-id> // create a new branch named for an issue, e.g. RHINDOC-123

$[issue-branch] git commit --allow-empty -m 'empty initial commit' // on issue branch, make an empty commit you will amend

☝️  suggested espanso trigger: `gce:`

